title: Birkenstock warns in IPO filing that knock-offs on Facebook are a top risk
description: The 249-year-old shoe company said in its IPO filing that knock-off brands have used social media to try and "trick users" into buying cheap fakes.

title: CDC clears updated Covid vaccines, allowing shots to start within days
description: CDC Director Mandy Cohen still has to sign off on the panel's recommendation before the new Pfizer and Moderna Covid vaccines become available nationwide.

title: Co-founder of $4 billion crypto fraud scheme gets 20 years in prison, 'Cryptoqueen' partner remains at large
description: Karl Greenwood's co-founder Ruja Ignatova, known as the "Cryptoqueen" on the FBI's Top 10 Most Wanted list, remains at large, the DOJ said.

title: House committee targets crackdown on U.S. investment in Chinese tech, military development
description: Rep. Mike Gallagher said U.S. companies continuing to invest in blacklisted Chinese firms are helping to fund the Chinese government's push to invade Taiwan.

title: Elizabeth Warren calls for an investigation into Musk and Starlink in Ukraine after biography claim
description: In his book titled "Elon Musk," released Tuesday, Walter Isaacson details Musk's policy of geofencing Starlink's satellite network over Crimea last year.

title: BP CEO Bernard Looney will resign, report says
description: The Financial Times reported the move Tuesday, citing two people with knowledge of the decision.

title: Oracle stock is poised for its steepest drop since 2002 on weak revenue guidance
description: Oracle shares plunged on Tuesday after the software maker missed analysts' estimates on revenue and issued weak guidance.

title: Demand for oil, gas and coal will peak by 2030, but that's not fast enough to keep global warming within 1.5 degrees, says IEA chief
description: Demand for fossil fuels are set to peak by 2030, says Fatih Birol, chief of the IEA. That's "nowhere near steep enough" to keep global warming to 1.5 degrees.

title: Bitcoin, helped by a possible short squeeze, rebounds from Monday's FTX-suspected slide
description: The price of bitcoin bounced on Tuesday, reversing losses from the previous day that were driven by fears of FTX liquidations.

title: Decongestant found in many cold, allergy medicines doesn’t actually work, FDA advisors say
description: In a unanimous vote, advisors said oral versions of phenylephrine – a nasal decongestant found in versions of drugs like Nyquil and Benadryl – isn't effective.

title: 2024 election ad spending expected to top $10 billion, smashing Biden-Trump 2020 record
description: The 2024 projection shows an increase of more than $1 billion from the record set in 2020 when then-President Donald Trump faced off against Joe Biden.

title: McCarthy directs GOP-led House committees to open Biden impeachment inquiry
description: McCarthy claimed Tuesday that Biden had lied to the American people about his knowledge of his family's foreign business dealings.

title: SpaceX’s near monopoly on rocket launches is a ‘huge concern,' Lazard banker warns
description: A Lazard investment banker sounded the alarm about the dominance of Elon Musk's SpaceX in the rocket launch market.

title: Taiwan chip giant TSMC to invest up to $100 million in Arm IPO
description: TSMC manufactures semiconductors for companies from Apple to Nvidia, that are often based on Arm architecture.

title: Russia's Putin praises Elon Musk as an 'outstanding person' and 'talented businessman'
description: Putin's comments come after Musk said last week that he refused an emergency request by Ukraine to extend coverage of Starlink satellites to the Crimea.

title: Alibaba CEO warns of being ‘displaced’ if the Chinese tech giant doesn’t keep up in AI
description: The new CEO Eddie Wu is laying out his strategic priorities for Alibaba.

title: Walter Isaacson's new Elon Musk biography is already taking off in China
description: Walter Isaacson's new biography of Elon Musk hit the Chinese market Tuesday.

title: Britain's $4.5 billion digital bank Monzo debuts investments feature
description: British digital bank Monzo has launched a feature that lets users invest with as little as £1.

title: With Putin and Kim Jong Un set to meet, the West fears what Russia and North Korea are planning
description: The leaders of North Korea and Russia are set to discuss deepening military, economic and geopolitical cooperation — but experts expect arms to be a key topic.

title: Gas markets are becoming 'extremely difficult' to predict. It's a big problem for Europe this winter
description: As Europe races to prepare for another winter heating season, energy analysts have warned volatile markets could send prices sharply higher.

title: Packaging giant Smurfit Kappa's shares fall 11% after WestRock merger announcement
description: The companies will form Smurfit WestRock — set to be one of the largest packaging companies in the world.

title: Elon Musk's 700 mph hyperloop tech hasn't become reality. But companies aren't giving up
description: Tesla founder Elon Musk came up with the hyperloop concept in 2013.

title: After Nvidia's 200% rally this year, investors look to the Arm IPO — but the two are very different
description: Softbank, the owner of Arm, and its positioning of the British chip designer as an AI play, ahead of its blockbuster initial public offering (IPO).

title: Why RTO mandates are layoffs in disguise, according to workplace experts: ‘Companies are daring employees to quit’
description: The need to induce soft layoffs could be driven by recession threats and changes related to consumer spending, workplace experts told CNBC Make It.

title: MGM Resorts is facing 'ongoing' cyber incident that sent reservation and booking systems offline
description: The casino and lodging operator said that its gaming operations were back online but gave no update on lodging or restaurant reservations.

title: GlobalFoundries opens $4 billion Singapore expansion fab to meet 'demand for essential semiconductor chips'
description: GlobalFoundries announced Tuesday the opening of its $4 billion expansion fabrication plant in Singapore.

title: Steve Forbes says the Fed's not going to cut rates soon
description: The Fed started its aggressive rate hike campaign in March 2022 as inflation climbed to its highest levels in 40 years.

title: How Luckin Coffee overtook Starbucks as the largest coffee chain in China
description: Luckin Coffee hit 10,000 stores in China in June, surpassing Starbucks as the largest coffee chain brand in the country following rapid nationwide expansion this year.
